<TEXT>
leftist guerrillas launched a 
series of attacks in the capital saturday leaving three people 
dead and at least 26 injured officials and witnesses said rebels 
said they targeted president alfredo cristianis official residence 
gunfire explosions and sirens could be heard throughout the 
city saturday night 
there are many people wounded by bullets and explosives but we 
have not gathered complete information because we have not been 
able to evacuate the wounded the combat is so intense a red 
cross spokesman said on condition of anonymity 
three red cross ambulances were either shot at or hit in the 
crossfire a spokesman for the group said two rescuers were 
injured when bullets hit the tires of one ambulance and it 
overturned he said 
an associated press photographer said he saw about 30 people 
wounded at the governments rosales hospital 
an employee of the armed forces press office speaking by 
telephone on condition of anonymity reported attacks 
everywhere but could not confirm their exact locations 
residents said they heard rifle fire near the homes of cristiani 
and ricardo alvarenga president of the legislative assembly and 
the rebels clandestine radio venceremos claimed attacks on both 
houses the official presidential residence was also attacked it 
said 
it was not immediately known whether the leaders were injured in 
the attacks but according to civilian sources the attack on 
alvarengas residence left at least one guerrilla dead and at two 
security guards wounded 
the attacks came three days after the farabundo marti national 
liberation front promised to intensify its decadeold insurgency 
against the usbacked government in which more than 70000 
people have been killed 
radio stations said rebels attacked installations of the armed 
forces joint chiefs of staff and military positions in the city of 
santa tecla west of the capital also reported hit were army or 
security force installations in the san salvador neighborhoods of 
mejicanos zacamil soyapango miramonte miralvalle montebello 
the national university and the catholic university 
some radio reports said four civilians were wounded in 
mejicanos they also said attacks were launched on the eastern 
cities of san miguel and usulutaan but military officials could 
not confirm it 
the first guerrilla attack came saturday morning when guerrillas 
launched six homemade mortars at the barracks in northern san 
salvador said col carlos carrillo director of the national 
guard he said one struck the installation injuring three soldiers 
another mortar landed in a poor neighborhood killing two 
children and injuring five civilians carrillo said 
he said the mortars had been placed in three vehicles at the 
barracks perimeter but technicians deactivated one before it 
exploded 
the attack was a demonstration of their the rebels 
inefficiency if they had planned it well all of their shots would 
have fallen inside the installations carrillo said 
however witnesses said one explosive hit a truck in the 
barracks and injured 10 soldiers 
carrillo said the rebel front was probably behind the attack 
the rebels did not claim responsibility 
guerrilla leaders said last week that they planned to intensify 
their attacks in el salvador the guerrillas attacked another 
military barracks oct 30 killing one person and injuring 15 
people 
rebel leader claim that cristiani is not interested in 
negotiating a solution to the conflict they also blame his 
rightist government for the oct 31 bombing of a union headquarters 
in san salvador that killed 10 people and injured more than 30 
recent peace talks between the government and the guerrilla 
front have not moved any closer to ending the war 
