<TEXT>
the mayors of east and west berlin shook hands 
sunday at a new berlin wall crossing point in a historic meeting 
symbolizing the crumbling of the cold war relic that divided the 
city since 1961 
their meeting came after more than 1 million east germans poured 
into west germany on saturday taking advantage of their 
governments opening of western borders the vast majority intended 
to make a brief visit and then return to the east 
on sunday west berlin mayor walter momper and his east berlin 
counterpart erhard krack met at the potsdamer platz a bleak 
virtual nomans land bisected by the berlin wall 
hours before their morning session east german workers drilled 
a hole through the wall with jackhammers at potsdamer platz 
creating the third new border crossing point since east germanys 
communist leaders announced the end of travel restrictions late 
last week 
momper and krack later left the area for breakfast and talks in 
a west berlin hotel 
the new freedom to travel and other reforms in east germany have 
touched off a wave of enthusiam about the possibility of reuniting 
the two german states divided at the end of world war ii 
however east german communist leader egon krenz on saturday 
dismissed such talk 
the new wave of visitors to west berlin and west germany on 
sunday was expected to exceed saturdays estimated 13 million 
visitors almost 8 percent of east germans 166 million population 
most of saturdays exuberant visitors returned home overnight 
west german border police said 
a core of east german and west berlin revelers kept a joyful 
vigil in front of the brandenburg gate on the western side of the 
berlin wall 
however west berlin riot police vans lined up in front of the 
wall at the brandenburg gate early sunday to try to fend off 
revelers who lit torches and candles in memory of east germans 
killed trying to escape over the wall 
at the friederichstrasse crossing point known as checkpoint 
charlie renowned cellist mstislav rostropovich gave an impromptu 
concert saturday in front of a section of the wall covered with 
graffiti 
police said a 24yearold visitor from potsdam east germany 
went into labor on bustling wuerttembergische strasse and gave 
birth to a girl on the sidewalk to the delight of a surrounding 
crowd 
chancellor helmut kohl of west germany said he would meet with 
krenz whose three weeks in office have brought a whirlwind of 
change to discuss ways of cooperating in the new age 
however krenz told kohl to forget any ideas of making the two 
nations that rose from the rubble of world war ii into a single 
germany again 
east germanys communist authorities built the 14foothigh 
berlin wall beginning aug 13 1961 to stem a flow of workers to 
the west ironically it was another flight this year of more than 
200000 east germans that forced them to open it 
east german leaders lifted travel regulations and pledged 
greater democratic freedoms after both the exodus and weeks of 
street protests 
</TEXT>
